00:24:11.910 --> 00:24:13.355 align:middle line:90%
making babies right away.

00:24:13.355 --> 00:24:16.560 align:middle line:84%
And you're supposed to actually
mate on the wedding night

00:24:16.560 --> 00:24:18.520 align:middle line:84%
and supposed to get
pregnant on the same night.

00:24:18.520 --> 00:24:20.340 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's the expectation.

00:24:20.340 --> 00:24:22.420 align:middle line:84%
So the very fact that I
didn't do any of that,

00:24:22.420 --> 00:24:24.820 align:middle line:84%
I was already not
fulfilling the requirement.

00:24:24.820 --> 00:24:27.645 align:middle line:84%
So I was worried about
being a good Muslim girl--

00:24:27.645 --> 00:24:29.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And wife and mother.

00:24:29.070 --> 00:24:30.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: --and everything else.

00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:31.570 align:middle line:90%
So for me, that was the goal.

00:24:31.570 --> 00:24:33.480 align:middle line:84%
But then my first
husband told me

00:24:33.480 --> 00:24:35.890 align:middle line:84%
that I prefer that you
get your education done,

00:24:35.890 --> 00:24:37.620 align:middle line:90%
you get your degree.

00:24:37.620 --> 00:24:39.730 align:middle line:90%
So I had to respect that.

00:24:39.730 --> 00:24:42.360 align:middle line:84%
So I did it out of
following my husband

00:24:42.360 --> 00:24:43.475 align:middle line:90%
as a good, obedient wife.

00:24:43.475 --> 00:24:44.850 align:middle line:84%
And I'm so glad
that he did that.

00:24:44.850 --> 00:24:45.767 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, so glad.

00:24:45.767 --> 00:24:47.350 align:middle line:90%
I mean, really, that was a gift.

00:24:47.350 --> 00:24:48.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: That was a gift.

00:24:48.010 --> 00:24:49.052 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That was grace.

00:24:49.052 --> 00:24:50.590 align:middle line:90%
UC, really good school.

00:24:50.590 --> 00:24:52.602 align:middle line:84%
And you ended up--
you were quite smart.

00:24:52.602 --> 00:24:55.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you got your degree in
two and a half years, right?

00:24:55.060 --> 00:24:55.370 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: Yes.

00:24:55.370 --> 00:24:56.412 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: In engineering?

00:24:56.412 --> 00:25:00.638 align:middle line:84%
>>SONI: Yes, and taught by
a Chinese professor, who

00:25:00.638 --> 00:25:01.930 align:middle line:90%
were not speaking good English.

00:25:01.930 --> 00:25:04.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it
was pretty amazing.

00:25:04.140 --> 00:25:06.250 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, you got a job
at Hughes Aeronautics,

00:25:06.250 --> 00:25:08.438 align:middle line:84%
went on to Boeing,
also ended up at NASA.

00:25:08.438 --> 00:25:09.730 align:middle line:90%
We'll talk about that in a bit.

00:25:09.730 --> 00:25:11.740 align:middle line:84%
But along the way,
you had two children,

00:25:11.740 --> 00:25:14.105 align:middle line:90%
one had some disability.

00:25:14.105 --> 00:25:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And so you had that going
on in your life, which is--

00:25:16.540 --> 00:25:20.280 align:middle line:84%
and you were working,
I assume, and trying

00:25:20.280 --> 00:25:22.750 align:middle line:84%
to learn to cook and do these
things a good wife does.

00:25:22.750 --> 00:25:27.378 align:middle line:84%
And then of all the good luck,
your mother-in-law moves in.

00:25:27.378 --> 00:25:30.010 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] Oh, goodness.

00:25:30.010 --> 00:25:32.733 align:middle line:84%
It's like if things
couldn't have gotten harder,

00:25:32.733 --> 00:25:34.650 align:middle line:84%
they became harder because
you couldn't really

00:25:34.650 --> 00:25:35.610 align:middle line:90%
please her, right?

00:25:35.610 --> 00:25:36.430 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: Right.

00:25:36.430 --> 00:25:38.930 align:middle line:84%
And that was the thing that
mother-in-law actually moved in.

00:25:38.930 --> 00:25:41.070 align:middle line:84%
Mainly the goal was
to get a lot of help

00:25:41.070 --> 00:25:44.050 align:middle line:84%
from her because that's
also a cultural mindset

00:25:44.050 --> 00:25:47.950 align:middle line:84%
because generally, nobody
raises their own children.

00:25:47.950 --> 00:25:49.750 align:middle line:84%
It's the whole culture,
the whole family,

00:25:49.750 --> 00:25:50.920 align:middle line:90%
the extended family raises.

00:25:50.920 --> 00:25:53.910 align:middle line:84%
So my husband actually
thought that it's good to have

00:25:53.910 --> 00:25:55.480 align:middle line:90%
a mother-in-law who basically--

00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:56.730 align:middle line:90%
I mean, his mother, of course.

00:25:56.730 --> 00:25:57.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Coming
from the right place.

00:25:57.940 --> 00:25:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>>SONI: Coming from the
right place and all of that.

00:25:59.560 --> 00:26:02.220 align:middle line:84%
And then generally, that's how
it is because they are also

00:26:02.220 --> 00:26:03.072 align:middle line:90%
well taken care of.

00:26:03.072 --> 00:26:04.530 align:middle line:84%
And then they're
also reciprocating

00:26:04.530 --> 00:26:06.098 align:middle line:90%
by taking care of your children.

00:26:06.098 --> 00:26:07.890 align:middle line:84%
It's just in my case,
the biggest challenge

00:26:07.890 --> 00:26:13.530 align:middle line:84%
was that my husband and his
mom, they were a very good unit.

00:26:13.530 --> 00:26:16.890 align:middle line:84%
They were so good unit that
it was a conflict of interest

00:26:16.890 --> 00:26:19.290 align:middle line:84%
because when you are so
good with your mother, then

00:26:19.290 --> 00:26:21.370 align:middle line:84%
you're not making any
decision with your partner.

00:26:21.370 --> 00:26:24.320 align:middle line:84%
And because of that and the
very fact that we were also

00:26:24.320 --> 00:26:25.570 align:middle line:90%
very different belief system--

00:26:25.570 --> 00:26:27.760 align:middle line:84%
I was not raised with
a religious mindset,

00:26:27.760 --> 00:26:29.110 align:middle line:90%
but he was very religious.

00:26:29.110 --> 00:26:30.870 align:middle line:84%
So I actually became
more religious

00:26:30.870 --> 00:26:34.050 align:middle line:84%
when I came to America,
which sounds very ironic.

00:26:34.050 --> 00:26:35.940 align:middle line:84%
While I was in Pakistan,
I had more freedom

00:26:35.940 --> 00:26:38.070 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to religion
because of my dad

00:26:38.070 --> 00:26:41.260 align:middle line:84%
because he wasn't like
so hung up on all that.

00:26:41.260 --> 00:26:43.050 align:middle line:84%
But having the
mother-in-law and then

00:26:43.050 --> 00:26:44.925 align:middle line:84%
having a husband who
travels all the time,

00:26:44.925 --> 00:26:47.050 align:middle line:84%
and then I felt like being
married to mother-in-law

00:26:47.050 --> 00:26:49.880 align:middle line:84%
than the husband, all of that
created a lot of friction

00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:50.680 align:middle line:90%
in my life.

00:26:50.680 --> 00:26:52.650 align:middle line:84%
And then working full-time
and then fulfilling

00:26:52.650 --> 00:26:54.540 align:middle line:84%
the expectation
of a mother-in-law

00:26:54.540 --> 00:26:58.380 align:middle line:84%
expects a daughter-in-law to
be, a typical daughter-in-law, I

00:26:58.380 --> 00:27:01.385 align:middle line:84%
mean, it's hard for that
person to be all of that.

00:27:01.385 --> 00:27:02.560 align:middle line:90%
How can you do all of that?

00:27:02.560 --> 00:27:05.370 align:middle line:84%
How can you be a homemaker
and also bring the income?

00:27:05.370 --> 00:27:06.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Work at Boeing.

00:27:06.850 --> 00:27:07.210 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:27:07.210 --> 00:27:08.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: Exactly.

00:27:08.010 --> 00:27:10.710 align:middle line:84%
And my income was
similar to my husband.

00:27:10.710 --> 00:27:13.890 align:middle line:84%
However, the respect
wasn't given the same.

00:27:13.890 --> 00:27:16.680 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, it was just
multiplying, multiplying

00:27:16.680 --> 00:27:18.610 align:middle line:84%
to the point where
when I had two kids,

00:27:18.610 --> 00:27:21.180 align:middle line:84%
it became very prominent
to me that I wasn't

00:27:21.180 --> 00:27:23.100 align:middle line:90%
very happy in the marriage.

00:27:23.100 --> 00:27:24.820 align:middle line:90%
And I needed some change.

00:27:24.820 --> 00:27:27.727 align:middle line:84%
And that's when the whole
world came to stop me.

00:27:27.727 --> 00:27:30.060 align:middle line:84%
My parents came to stop me,
of course, my mother-in-law.

00:27:30.060 --> 00:27:31.925 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because you can't
get divorced in that culture.

00:27:31.925 --> 00:27:33.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: No, not at all.

00:27:33.010 --> 00:27:34.338 align:middle line:90%
Nobody has ever done it.

00:27:34.338 --> 00:27:35.255 align:middle line:90%
Nobody's ever done it.

00:27:35.255 --> 00:27:38.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But interestingly,
your dad, of all people,

00:27:38.400 --> 00:27:40.840 align:middle line:90%
understood.

00:27:40.840 --> 00:27:43.140 align:middle line:84%
He was the one when he came
and observed at close head

00:27:43.140 --> 00:27:47.260 align:middle line:84%
and saw, his kind of a broken
heart that he had for you said,

00:27:47.260 --> 00:27:48.850 align:middle line:90%
no, you can do this.

00:27:48.850 --> 00:27:50.290 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: Yeah.

00:27:50.290 --> 00:27:51.780 align:middle line:84%
That was actually--
I think there

00:27:51.780 --> 00:27:54.210 align:middle line:84%
was a healing moment for
me because all my life,

00:27:54.210 --> 00:27:57.960 align:middle line:84%
I actually didn't like how
my dad was with me, partly

00:27:57.960 --> 00:28:00.630 align:middle line:84%
because he was so
angry at everyone.

00:28:00.630 --> 00:28:03.915 align:middle line:84%
And he wasn't letting me
do what I wanted to do.

00:28:03.915 --> 00:28:05.590 align:middle line:84%
And it had nothing
to do with me.

00:28:05.590 --> 00:28:09.330 align:middle line:84%
It had everything to do with him
because everybody is projecting

00:28:09.330 --> 00:28:11.010 align:middle line:90%
their own fear on you.

00:28:11.010 --> 00:28:12.160 align:middle line:90%
And that was the case.

00:28:12.160 --> 00:28:14.160 align:middle line:84%
But that, I think,
moment when he actually

00:28:14.160 --> 00:28:15.550 align:middle line:90%
said that it doesn't matter--

00:28:15.550 --> 00:28:18.060 align:middle line:84%
he said that I don't think I
can support you financially

00:28:18.060 --> 00:28:20.220 align:middle line:84%
or I can support
you emotionally.

00:28:20.220 --> 00:28:22.485 align:middle line:90%
But I will approve--

00:28:22.485 --> 00:28:25.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to respect your
decision whether you stay

00:28:25.170 --> 00:28:27.360 align:middle line:84%
or whether you don't,
because I've seen enough

00:28:27.360 --> 00:28:30.602 align:middle line:84%
that I feel like that if this is
how you get treated while we are

00:28:30.602 --> 00:28:33.310 align:middle line:84%
here, we don't even know how you
get treated when we're not here.

00:28:33.310 --> 00:28:37.060 align:middle line:84%
And that to me right there
was the moment in my life

00:28:37.060 --> 00:28:39.730 align:middle line:84%
that really like
a giant crossroad.

00:28:39.730 --> 00:28:43.470 align:middle line:84%
I was like, oh my God, I was
so happy that my dad approved.

00:28:43.470 --> 00:28:44.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:28:44.440 --> 00:28:47.330 align:middle line:84%
So you freed yourself
from the marriage.

00:28:47.330 --> 00:28:51.220 align:middle line:84%
And so your career, let's talk
a little bit about what you

00:28:51.220 --> 00:28:53.830 align:middle line:90%
were particularly skilled in.

00:28:53.830 --> 00:28:56.300 align:middle line:84%
You were involved with
software development,

00:28:56.300 --> 00:28:57.500 align:middle line:90%
as I recall in the book.

00:28:57.500 --> 00:29:00.010 align:middle line:84%
But explain to people
how it progressed

00:29:00.010 --> 00:29:01.520 align:middle line:90%
in the aeronautics industry.

00:29:01.520 --> 00:29:02.320 align:middle line:90%
What was your role?

00:29:02.320 --> 00:29:04.820 align:middle line:84%
>>SONI: So basically,
as a bachelor--

00:29:04.820 --> 00:29:06.710 align:middle line:84%
I have a bachelor in
electrical engineering.

00:29:06.710 --> 00:29:08.680 align:middle line:84%
But when I got
hired by the Hughes,

00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:09.910 align:middle line:90%
it was a satellite phone.

00:29:09.910 --> 00:29:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And they were looking
for software engineer.

00:29:11.780 --> 00:29:13.730 align:middle line:84%
So of course, I wasn't
a software engineer.

00:29:13.730 --> 00:29:15.260 align:middle line:84%
But they said, well,
you're electrical engineer,

00:29:15.260 --> 00:29:16.310 align:middle line:90%
you can learn anything.

00:29:16.310 --> 00:29:18.940 align:middle line:84%
And then they taught me all
the programs that I had to use

00:29:18.940 --> 00:29:24.380 align:middle line:84%
to code in Ada and C and
C++ and machine language.

00:29:24.380 --> 00:29:26.560 align:middle line:84%
So basically, it was
actually a perfect job for me

00:29:26.560 --> 00:29:29.050 align:middle line:84%
because I was an electrical
engineer who learned

00:29:29.050 --> 00:29:30.290 align:middle line:90%
how to be software engineer.

00:29:30.290 --> 00:29:33.520 align:middle line:84%
In that three year, I learned
the entire cradle-to-grave

00:29:33.520 --> 00:29:34.610 align:middle line:90%
software life cycle.

00:29:34.610 --> 00:29:37.090 align:middle line:84%
I learned how the
bits and bytes makes

00:29:37.090 --> 00:29:39.110 align:middle line:90%
anything happen in the world.

00:29:39.110 --> 00:29:40.750 align:middle line:84%
And that to me was
the best experience

00:29:40.750 --> 00:29:43.080 align:middle line:84%
that I have to say,
thank you, Hughes,

00:29:43.080 --> 00:29:44.330 align:middle line:90%
for giving me that experience.

00:29:44.330 --> 00:29:46.747 align:middle line:84%
But I also want to go a little
farther for everybody who's

00:29:46.747 --> 00:29:49.330 align:middle line:84%
listening, is the reason I
got that experience because I

00:29:49.330 --> 00:29:52.040 align:middle line:84%
was getting a-- it was very
hard for me to get an interview.

00:29:52.040 --> 00:29:53.920 align:middle line:84%
I was sending
hundreds and hundreds

00:29:53.920 --> 00:29:56.970 align:middle line:84%
of resumes because of my name,
because my last name was not

00:29:56.970 --> 00:29:57.770 align:middle line:90%
Soni.

00:29:57.770 --> 00:30:00.770 align:middle line:84%
It was Bandukwala, which
made it even harder.

00:30:00.770 --> 00:30:02.450 align:middle line:84%
When I would usually
get an interview,

00:30:02.450 --> 00:30:03.740 align:middle line:90%
I would usually get a job.

00:30:03.740 --> 00:30:07.750 align:middle line:84%
But when I would get a job, I
was not gung ho about the job

00:30:07.750 --> 00:30:10.600 align:middle line:90%
just because I got it.

00:30:10.600 --> 00:30:12.520 align:middle line:84%
In my heart, I knew
that there is a job

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:14.020 align:middle line:90%
that I'm going to feel for.

00:30:14.020 --> 00:30:15.800 align:middle line:84%
And that job has
to line up with me.

00:30:15.800 --> 00:30:18.220 align:middle line:84%
So I actually waited
for the right job.

00:30:18.220 --> 00:30:20.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's what triggered
me to always work

00:30:20.740 --> 00:30:23.230 align:middle line:84%
on the state-of-the-art
programs.

00:30:23.230 --> 00:30:25.190 align:middle line:84%
And I have done that
pretty much all my life.

00:30:25.190 --> 00:30:30.730 align:middle line:84%
I've worked on programs that are
very unique and that are very--

00:30:30.730 --> 00:30:34.200 align:middle line:90%
like to change technologically.

00:30:34.200 --> 00:30:36.460 align:middle line:90%
It's like a big milestone.

00:30:36.460 --> 00:30:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And that has been
my record, which

00:30:38.820 --> 00:30:42.226 align:middle line:84%
is the reason I'm doing
what I'm doing now.

00:30:42.226 --> 00:30:44.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so we
have a little insight

00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:48.130 align:middle line:84%
into how your mind works,
how your spirit works.

00:30:48.130 --> 00:30:49.300 align:middle line:90%
You get divorced.

00:30:49.300 --> 00:30:52.360 align:middle line:84%
Now, ultimately, you
did remarry, right?

00:30:52.360 --> 00:30:53.160 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: Yes.

00:30:53.160 --> 00:30:57.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And your
kids stayed with you.

00:30:57.190 --> 00:30:58.590 align:middle line:90%
The kids stayed with you.

00:30:58.590 --> 00:31:02.320 align:middle line:84%
And then ultimately,
you ended up with NASA.

00:31:02.320 --> 00:31:03.570 align:middle line:90%
Now, how did that--

00:31:03.570 --> 00:31:05.910 align:middle line:84%
Boeing, doing similar
things, software design

00:31:05.910 --> 00:31:08.380 align:middle line:84%
for Boeing, software
engineering with Boeing.

00:31:08.380 --> 00:31:10.720 align:middle line:90%
And then you moved on to NASA.

00:31:10.720 --> 00:31:13.200 align:middle line:84%
So tell us about that
piece because that's always

00:31:13.200 --> 00:31:14.080 align:middle line:90%
quite impressive.

00:31:14.080 --> 00:31:15.890 align:middle line:84%
You have to be pretty
darn smart to get there.

00:31:15.890 --> 00:31:17.130 align:middle line:84%
>>SONI: So actually,
the interesting thing

00:31:17.130 --> 00:31:19.870 align:middle line:84%
is that as soon as I left Hughes
and started working at Boeing,

00:31:19.870 --> 00:31:22.270 align:middle line:84%
the first project was
International Space Station.

00:31:22.270 --> 00:31:24.430 align:middle line:84%
And that project was
directly with NASA.

00:31:24.430 --> 00:31:26.377 align:middle line:90%
So we were traveling to Houston.

00:31:26.377 --> 00:31:27.460 align:middle line:90%
We were working with them.

00:31:27.460 --> 00:31:28.835 align:middle line:84%
We were testing
all the computer.

00:31:28.835 --> 00:31:31.567 align:middle line:84%
So NASA was my customer
from that point on.

00:31:31.567 --> 00:31:33.150 align:middle line:84%
So I was already
interacting with NASA

00:31:33.150 --> 00:31:35.850 align:middle line:84%
in that capacity as
a Boeing employee.

00:31:35.850 --> 00:31:37.270 align:middle line:84%
And for the most
part, I've worked

00:31:37.270 --> 00:31:40.420 align:middle line:84%
on both commercial programs
and both secret programs

00:31:40.420 --> 00:31:43.270 align:middle line:84%
where either my customer has
been NASA or Missile Defense

00:31:43.270 --> 00:31:44.090 align:middle line:90%
Agency.

00:31:44.090 --> 00:31:46.970 align:middle line:84%
So that has been going
on for 20 odd years.

00:31:46.970 --> 00:31:50.030 align:middle line:84%
And then when I retired
from Boeing in 2018,

00:31:50.030 --> 00:31:52.900 align:middle line:84%
I was attending a wedding
where one of the girls

00:31:52.900 --> 00:31:54.940 align:middle line:90%
just liked my personality.

00:31:54.940 --> 00:31:57.790 align:middle line:90%
And she had a small company.

00:31:57.790 --> 00:32:00.620 align:middle line:84%
And they were looking for-
a fill in a role at NASA.

00:32:00.620 --> 00:32:02.040 align:middle line:90%
And I gave my resume.

00:32:02.040 --> 00:32:04.540 align:middle line:84%
And then it was interesting
because they had like five roles

00:32:04.540 --> 00:32:06.160 align:middle line:84%
that I could do,
partly because I

00:32:06.160 --> 00:32:07.760 align:middle line:84%
changed my role
every two and a half,

00:32:07.760 --> 00:32:09.530 align:middle line:90%
three years in my industry.

00:32:09.530 --> 00:32:11.703 align:middle line:84%
So therefore, I have
collected a lot--

00:32:11.703 --> 00:32:13.245 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Huge
experience background.

00:32:13.245 --> 00:32:13.900 align:middle line:90%
>>SONI: Huge experience.

00:32:13.900 --> 00:32:15.358 align:middle line:84%
So I could pretty
much do any role.

